In this article, President Donald Trump pardons Alice Johnson, who was previously given a life sentence for a nonviolent offense. Trump commuted her sentence earlier, and now he is granting her a full pardon. Johnson has been actively involved in advocating for other prisoners who she believes have also received unjustly long sentences. Pastor Robert Jeffress is present and offers a prayer, thanking God for the pardon and asking for blessings for Johnson and her family. Trump expresses his appreciation for Jeffress' prayer and congratulates Johnson on her pardon. The article concludes with the time of the event.